Document: AudioEffectLimiter  
Path: godot/classes/class_audioeffectlimiter.rst  
Summary: Properties and methods for controlling audio limiting behavior, including threshold, ceiling, and soft clipping parameters.  

ceiling_db (float): The waveform's maximum allowed value, in dB. Value can range from -20 to -0.1. Default: -0.1. Set via set_ceiling_db(value: float), get via get_ceiling_db().  

soft_clip_db (float): Modifies the volume of the limited waves, in dB. Value can range from 0 to 6. Default: 2.0. Set via set_soft_clip_db(value: float), get via get_soft_clip_db().  

soft_clip_ratio (float): This property has no effect on the audio. Use AudioEffectHardLimiter instead, as this Limiter effect is deprecated. Default: 10.0. Set via set_soft_clip_ratio(value: float), get via get_soft_clip_ratio().  

threshold_db (float): The volume threshold level from which the limiter begins to be active, in dB. Value can range from -30 to 0. Default: 0.0. Set via set_threshold_db(value: float), get via get_threshold_db().  

Note: soft_clip_ratio is deprecated and should not be used. Use AudioEffectHardLimiter for relevant functionality.